features: ★【Nostalgic Retro Design】Revisit the charm of classic vinyl records with our vintage-inspired coaster set, meticulously crafted to bring back the essence of the golden era of music. This collection includes six coasters designed as authentic vinyl records, complete with a holder resembling a vintage record player, creating a captivating throwback ambiance for your space.

★【Ideal Gifts for Music Lovers】These coasters capture the essence of the 80s in a cool manner, perfectly replicating the allure of classic records, our coasters serve as an ideal decorative touch, infusing any setting with a unique coolness that's particularly appealing for music enthusiasts seeking a nostalgic vibe.

★【Durability and Easy Maintenance】Crafted from high-quality vinyl material, our coasters boast durability and reliability. Each coaster features a non-slip rubber pad underneath, ensuring stability, heat resistance, lightweight handling, and effortless maintenance. Simply wipe away stains or wash them with water for a fuss-free cleanup.

★【Versatile and Protective】Accommodating various cup sizes and shapes, suitable for all types of cups, mugs, and glasses. our versatile coasters safeguard your furniture from beverage-induced damage. Elevate your space with a hint of nostalgia while preserving your tabletops.

★【Unmatched Sales Support】Backed by 5 years after-sales service guarantee, our commitment to customer satisfaction is unwavering. Feel free to get in touch with us anytime for prompt assistance with any product-related issues.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: For the price it was adorable! I got this for my family member who loves vinyl’s. They look just like real ones but just mini versions! They also do a great job keeping the water off tables.Adorable and do their job!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Made a Great Gift
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a gift for someone that loves Vinyl Records and they loved this coaster set. They loved the look and they are excited for the opportunity to use it. Over all it is built pretty well. The coasters themselves feel substantial. The tonearm is made of plastic so you can't be too rough with it. You need to gently turn that to the side to get the coasters off. I would recommend this coaster set to anyone looking for a fun coaster set and especially for those vinyl lovers in your life.
